==Chinese==
{{zh-forms|alt=𠣙,𠣡}}

===Glyph origin===
{{Han etyl}}

{{Han compound|螾|日|t2=sun; day|ls=psc|c1=p|c2=s}}.

The pictographic protoform of {{zh-l|*螾}} was borrowed to represent "period of days" in oracle bone script. In bronze inscriptions, the semantic component {{zh-l|*日|sun/day}} was added to this character. In the Warring States period, the phonetic component was mistaken as {{zh-l|*勹|bow down}}, hence the incorrect analysis in ''{{w|Shuowen Jiezi}}'' of this character as {{Han compound|勹|日}}.

